[[cdo:5 nguŏk 3 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 3 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:五月初三]] {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 3''' is the 3rd day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[弘仁]] 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[819]] {{ill|May 30|ja|5月30日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|12=draft|12=draft}} began the establishment of the head temple of Shingon Buddhism at {{ill|Kōyasan|ja|高野山|12=draft|12=draft}}, founding the headquarters of the Shingon sect, {{ill|Kongōbu-ji|ja|金剛峯寺|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1592]] {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the first Korean expedition led by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|12=draft|12=draft}}, the vanguard forces including {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|ja|小西行長|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Katō Kiyomasa|ja|加藤清正|12=draft|12=draft}} entered Hanseong (present-day [[Seoul]]); * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|June 22|ja|6月22日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The formation of the Ōu Reppan Dōmei (the alliance of 33 domains from northern Japan) during the Boshin War, uniting anti-bakufu forces in the region.
== Births == * [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1340]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Mototada|ja|足利基氏|12=draft|12=draft}}, the second son of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|足利尊氏|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[1367]]). * [[永正]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1511]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|ja|足利義晴|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[1550]]). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kawakami Bēzan|ja|川上眉山|12=draft|12=draft}}, a novelist (died [[1908]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kempo (era)|Kempo]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1213]] {{ill|May 24|ja|5月24日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Wada Yoshimori|ja|和田義盛|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and the first Shitashō-bettō of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1147]]).
