'''May 3''' is the 3rd day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* [[弘仁]] 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[819]] {{ill|May 30|ja|5月30日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=|12=draft}} began the establishment of the head temple of Shingon Buddhism at {{ill|Kōyasan|ja|高野山|qq=|12=draft}}, founding the headquarters of the Shingon sect, {{ill|Kongōbu-ji|ja|金剛峯寺|qq=|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1592]] {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|qq=|12=draft}}) – In the first Korean expedition led by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|qq=|12=draft}}, the vanguard forces including {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|ja|小西行長|qq=|12=draft}} and {{ill|Katō Kiyomasa|ja|加藤清正|qq=|12=draft}} entered Hanseong (present-day [[Seoul]]); 
* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|June 22|ja|6月22日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The formation of the Ōu Reppan Dōmei (the alliance of 33 domains from northern Japan) during the Boshin War, uniting anti-bakufu forces in the region.

== Births ==
* [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1340]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Mototada|ja|足利基氏|qq=|12=draft}}, the second son of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|足利尊氏|qq=|12=draft}}, and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[1367]]).
* [[永正]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1511]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|ja|足利義晴|qq=|12=draft}}, the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[1550]]).
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kawakami Bēzan|ja|川上眉山|qq=|12=draft}}, a novelist (died [[1908]]).

== Deaths ==
* [[Kempo (era)|Kempo]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1213]] {{ill|May 24|ja|5月24日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Wada Yoshimori|ja|和田義盛|qq=|12=draft}}, a military commander and the first Shitashō-bettō of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1147]]).


