{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月初三|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 3일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 3''' is the 3rd day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[弘仁]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[819]] [[:en:May 30|May 30]]) – [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] began the establishment of the head temple of Shingon Buddhism at [[:en:Mount Kōya|Kōyasan]], founding the headquarters of the Shingon sect, [[:en:Kongōbu-ji|Kongōbu-ji]]. * [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1592]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – In the first Korean expedition led by [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]], the vanguard forces including [[:en:Konishi Yukinaga|Konishi Yukinaga]] and [[:en:Katō Kiyomasa|Katō Kiyomasa]] entered Hanseong (present-day [[Seoul]]); * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=}} ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – The formation of the Ōu Reppan Dōmei (the alliance of 33 domains from northern Japan) during the Boshin War, uniting anti-bakufu forces in the region.
== Births == * [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1340]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Motouji|Ashikaga Mototada]], the second son of [[:en:Ashikaga Takauji|Ashikaga Takauji]], and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[1367]]). * [[永正]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1511]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiharu|Ashikaga Yoshiharu]], the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[1550]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Bizan Kawakami|Kawakami Bēzan]], a novelist (died [[1908]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kempo (era)|Kempo]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1213]] [[:en:May 24|May 24]]) – [[:en:Wada Yoshimori|Wada Yoshimori]], a military commander and the first Shitashō-bettō of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[1147]]).
