== Events == * [[弘仁]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[819]] [[:en:May 30|May 30]]) – [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] began the establishment of the head temple of Shingon Buddhism at [[:en:Mount Kōya|Kōyasan]], founding the headquarters of the Shingon sect, [[:en:Kongōbu-ji|Kongōbu-ji]]. * [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1592]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – In the first Korean expedition led by [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]], the vanguard forces including [[:en:Konishi Yukinaga|Konishi Yukinaga]] and [[:en:Katō Kiyomasa|Katō Kiyomasa]] entered Hanseong (present-day [[Seoul]]); * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年}}[[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]] ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – The formation of the Ōu Reppan Dōmei (the alliance of 33 domains from northern Japan) during the Boshin War, uniting anti-bakufu forces in the region.
== Births == * [[Ryakuō]] 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1340|1340]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Motouji|Ashikaga Mototada]], the second son of [[:en:Ashikaga Takauji|Ashikaga Takauji]], and the first Kamakura Kubō (died [[:en:1367|1367]]). * [[永正]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1511|1511]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiharu|Ashikaga Yoshiharu]], the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died [[:en:1550|1550]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Bizan Kawakami|Kawakami Bēzan]], a novelist (died [[1908]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kempo (era)|Kempo]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1213|1213]] [[:en:May 24|May 24]]) – [[:en:Wada Yoshimori|Wada Yoshimori]], a military commander and the first Shitashō-bettō of the Kamakura shogunate (born [[:en:1147|1147]]).
