'''May 3''' is the 3rd day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshū|qid=Q96759839|1=senshū}}{{efn|ja|先勝|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|弘仁|en|弘仁|qid=Q117599407|lt=弘仁|1=弘仁}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|819|en|819|qid=Q30343|lt=819|1=819}} {{ill|May 30|en|May 30|qid=Q2590|lt=May 30|1=May 30}}) – {{ill|Kūkai|en|Kūkai|qid=Q222227|lt=Kūkai|1=Kūkai}} began the establishment of the head temple of Shingon Buddhism at {{ill|Mount Kōya|en|Mount Kōya|qid=Q535065|lt=Kōyasan|1=Mount Kōya}}, founding the headquarters of the Shingon sect, {{ill|Kongōbu-ji|en|Kongōbu-ji|qid=Q1203429|lt=Kongōbu-ji|1=Kongōbu-ji}}.
* {{ill|Bunroku|en|Bunroku|qid=Q1373039|lt=Bunroku|1=Bunroku}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1592|en|1592|qid=Q6769|lt=1592|1=1592}} {{ill|June 12|en|June 12|qid=Q2619|lt=June 12|1=June 12}}) – In the first Korean expedition led by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|en|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qid=Q187550|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}}, the vanguard forces including {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|en|Konishi Yukinaga|qid=Q942553|lt=Konishi Yukinaga|1=Konishi Yukinaga}} and {{ill|Katō Kiyomasa|en|Katō Kiyomasa|qid=Q1069843|lt=Katō Kiyomasa|1=Katō Kiyomasa}} entered Hanseong (present-day {{ill|Seoul|en|Seoul|qid=Q8684|lt=Seoul|1=Seoul}}); 
* {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|1=1868|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q7717}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|June 22|en|June 22|qid=Q2663|lt=June 22|1=June 22}}) – The formation of the Ōu Reppan Dōmei (the alliance of 33 domains from northern Japan) during the Boshin War, uniting anti-bakufu forces in the region.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Ryakuō|en|Ryakuō|qid=Q1146182|lt=Ryakuō|1=Ryakuō}} 3rd year / [[興国]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1340|en|1340|qid=Q6056|lt=1340|1=1340}} {{ill|April 2|en|April 2|qid=Q2511|lt=April 2|1=April 2}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Motouji|en|Ashikaga Motouji|qid=Q4306921|lt=Ashikaga Mototada|1=Ashikaga Motouji}}, the second son of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|en|Ashikaga Takauji|qid=Q297107|lt=Ashikaga Takauji|1=Ashikaga Takauji}}, and the first Kamakura Kubō (died {{ill|1367|en|1367|qid=Q6202|lt=1367|1=1367}}).
* [[:en:永正|永正]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1511|en|1511|qid=Q6188|lt=1511|1=1511}} {{ill|April 2|en|April 2|qid=Q2511|lt=April 2|1=April 2}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|en|Ashikaga Yoshiharu|qid=Q536313|lt=Ashikaga Yoshiharu|1=Ashikaga Yoshiharu}}, the 12th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (died {{ill|1550|en|1550|qid=Q6557|lt=1550|1=1550}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1869|en|1869|qid=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}} {{ill|April 16|en|April 16|qid=Q2519|lt=April 16|1=April 16}}) – {{ill|Bizan Kawakami|en|Bizan Kawakami|qid=Q529950|lt=Kawakami Bēzan|1=Bizan Kawakami}}, a novelist (died {{ill|1908|en|1908|qid=Q2056|lt=1908|1=1908}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kempo (era)|en|Kempo (era)|qid=Q1194251|lt=Kempo|1=Kempo (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1213|en|1213|qid=Q5261|lt=1213|1=1213}} {{ill|May 24|en|May 24|qid=Q2584|lt=May 24|1=May 24}}) – {{ill|Wada Yoshimori|en|Wada Yoshimori|qid=Q3564968|lt=Wada Yoshimori|1=Wada Yoshimori}}, a military commander and the first Shitashō-bettō of the Kamakura shogunate (born {{ill|1147|en|1147|qid=Q19629|lt=1147|1=1147}}).

